Mistake.
I drastically over developed this roll of film by accident. I was so angry with myself that I didn't even look at the film for 3 months. 
When I finally decided to have a look I discovered this frame. To my surprise I was able to get a somewhat usable image, if you don't mind lots of grain and contrast.
Lesson learned.

Language of art. It's been said that an artist's work is a window into the soul of the subject and creator. I tend to agree. For me (a person for whom words often fail) images like this tell a story that I simply can't tell with words. Art for me is the story told between the lines. Portrait of Joy. July 2019. One of my favourite stories. #repost #gaze #connection #portraitphotography #thoseeyes #chapters #art #momentintime #stories

Nudes in the Landscape. These images featuring the wonderful @astridadventure. Not too long after these images were taken a couple storms would roll through that would cut our trip short and leave us with memories that will last a life time. The second storm was a bitch. The storm tossed our canoes in the air like they were nothing. My canoe was found in the next bay!! and brought back by rescuers. One tent was trashed having had it's tent poles snapped in two. During the storm I had to put my rain gear on inside my tent. The force of the winds simply pushed the water through the tent while I did my best to keep the sides of the tent from caving in on me. I kept thinking about the huge dead tree that I had set up my tent fairly close to. Not fun. The things we go through for art😉.
